Resolve issues with a custom skill not working with Cognitive Search

Building a custom skill gives you a way to insert transformations unique to your content. A custom skill executes independently, applying whatever enrichment step you require. For example, you could build custom classification models to differentiate business and financial contracts and documents, or add a speech recognition skill to reach deeper into audio files for relevant content.

If you're experiencing issues with a custom skill not working with Cognitive Search, use the following guidance to help resolve your issues.

Troubleshooting steps

If you are having trouble with a custom skill, ensure that:

  1. Your skill works with a REST client.
  2. The custom skill meets the custom skill interface guidelines.
  3. All indexer run errors and warnings are resolved.
  4. The skillset definition of the custom skill is valid.
  5. The input data matches the schema of your target index. For more information, see Field mappings and transformations using Azure Cognitive Search indexers.
  6. You use debug sessions to identify and resolve errors, validate changes, and push changes to a production skillset in the AI enrichment pipeline.

Resources

  • How to add a custom skill to a cognitive search pipeline
